  "coverage_note": "12 real named/standard-class vessels collected across all 5 SCOPE types: VLCC (Almi 320k DSME, Almi 315.5k HSHI, Alaska-class), Suezmax (Almi 158k DSME, GSI Greenway 158k LNG dual-fuel), Aframax (Almi 115k DSME, MV Prestige), LNG carriers (Mozah Q-Max, Hoegh Esperanza, standard 174k membrane class), LPG/VLGC (LPGC Ayame, standard 84k VLGC). LAYER 1 (principal particulars) is well-covered with cited values for LOA, beam, draft, deadweight, GT, cargo capacity from public Wikipedia pages, VesselFinder/Marine Insight news, and the Almi Tankers 2018 brochure PDF (extracted via pdftotext: LOA, beam, summer draft, DWT, lightship, GT all directly published). LBP is almost universally a gap (rarely published in brochures/encyclopedias). Depth is published for some (Prestige 18.7, Gastor 26.14, Hoegh 26) and gap/estimated for others. Block coefficient is NEVER published in these sources -> all marked estimated with typical class ranges (VLCC/Suezmax/Aframax ~0.82-0.83; LNG/LPG ~0.78). LAYER 2 (mass properties) is essentially unpublished as required by the brief: LCG/VCG are gaps everywhere (require trim/stability booklets, not public); TCG=0 (centreline symmetry, geometric fact); radii of gyration kxx/kyy/kzz are ALL marked estimated:<relation> using standard naval-architecture empirical relations (kxx=0.33-0.40*beam for roll, higher for wide LNG/LPG forms; kyy=kzz=0.25*Lpp for pitch/yaw) sourced to the TU Delft IMDC 2024 rolling-period paper conventions -- NO bare invented numbers. Displacement is estimated (DWT+lightship) where lightship is published (Almi 320k VLCC: 44,900 mt -> ~364,000 displacement) and gap otherwise. DATA-QUALITY FLAG: Wikipedia LPGC Ayame lists depth 11.6 m / draft 15.5 m which is physically implausible for a 230 m VLGC (depth < draft); cross-checked against standard 84k VLGC particulars (depth ~22.2, draft ~11.5) and flagged the swap in the record. The Almi brochure also yields additional un-recorded sisters (multiple identical Suezmax/Aframax/VLCC hulls) if more entities needed. PAYWALLED/UNAVAILABLE: ResearchGate 325k VLCC spec table (HTTP 403), Scribd GTT Mark III & 320k VLCC spec docs (landing pages only, full data behind login), GAS FORM C for BW Messina LPG carrier (404). No GHS/stability-booklet level mass-property data is publicly available for any of these vessels -- this is the inherent limitation flagged in the brief.",
